Subject: [PATCH 1/2] vfio: Create vfio_fs_type with inode per device
Date: Thu, 23 May 2024 13:56:26 -0600
Message-ID: <20240523195629.218043-2-alex.williamson@redhat.com>
In-Reply-To: <20240523195629.218043-1-alex.williamson@redhat.com>
References: <20240523195629.218043-1-alex.williamson@redhat.com>
Precedence: bulk
X-Mailing-List: kvm@vger.kernel.org
List-Id: <kvm.vger.kernel.org>
List-Subscribe: <mailto:kvm+subscribe@vger.kernel.org>
List-Unsubscribe: <mailto:kvm+unsubscribe@vger.kernel.org>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
X-Scanned-By: MIMEDefang 3.4.1 on 10.11.54.9

By linking all the device fds we provide to userspace to an
address space through a new pseudo fs, we can use tools like
unmap_mapping_range() to zap all vmas associated with a device.

Suggested-by: Jason Gunthorpe <jgg@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Williamson <alex.williamson@redhat.com>
